EFF leader, Julius Malema has called on Zimbabwe’s leaders to respect the wishes of the late Robert Mugabe and allow the youth to continue to pursue his legacy.  Malema has visited the Mugabe family in Harare to pay his respects. Mugabe died at the age of 95 from prostate cancer. His funeral was held more than a week ago and the body is expected to be interred at Heroes Acre in the capital within the next few weeks.  Malema, who had called on Mugabe to step down, says it is regrettable that the liberation fighter had to be removed by the Zimbabwe military…